// Base64-encoded copies of the "There Is Power in the Blood" Song Trainer's
// MIDI files, found in midi/power-in-the-blood-*.mid, embedded directly so
// the Song Player tab works when the site is opened straight from the file
// system (the browser blocks fetch() against local files under the file://
// protocol). Keyed by the same file-slug used for
// midi/power-in-the-blood-<slug>.mid (e.g. "C", "Cs", "D", ...).
//
// Each file is a brand-new two-hand arrangement of the classic Lewis E.
// Jones gospel hymn "There Is Power in the Blood" (1899, public domain),
// re-harmonized for this lesson so the left hand has a mix of major AND
// minor triads to practice, not just major ones:
//   - MIDI channel 0 (right hand): the hymn's soprano melody line, exactly
//     as sung, transposed into each of the 12 keys.
//   - MIDI channel 1 (left hand): a new block-chord accompaniment built
//     entirely from closed-position root triads — mostly the hymn's
//     original I - IV - V harmony, but with three of the repeated tonic
//     chords swapped for its relative minor (vi) and one for the
//     supertonic minor (ii) so a learner practices both chord qualities
//     under the same melody. Every chord is a plain major or minor triad
//     (root, 3rd, 5th) — no sevenths or inversions — to keep the left-hand
//     shapes simple and consistent with the rest of this app's chord
//     lessons.
// Both hands are read from the same file by loadMidiFileFromBase64() /
// parseMidiFile() in midi-file-reader.js, which now tags every parsed note
// with the MIDI channel it came from — the Song Trainer uses that to color
// the right hand and left hand differently on the keyboard.
const POWER_IN_THE_BLOOD_MIDI_DATA = {
  "C": '',
  "Cs": '',
  "D": '',
  "Ds": '',
  "E": '',
  "F": '',
  "Fs": '',
  "G": '',
  "Gs": '',
  "A": '',
  "As": '',
  "B": '',
};

// Base64-encoded copies of the "His Eye Is on the Sparrow" Song Trainer's
// MIDI files, found in midi/his-eye-is-on-the-sparrow-*.mid, embedded directly
// so the Song Player tab works when the site is opened straight from the file
// system (the browser blocks fetch() against local files under the file://
// protocol). Keyed by the same file-slug used for
// midi/his-eye-is-on-the-sparrow-<slug>.mid (e.g. "C", "Cs", "D", ...).
//
// Unlike the Power in the Blood lesson's purpose-built accompaniment, this
// file is the real 1905 Charles H. Gabriel hymn arrangement (Civilla D.
// Martin, words), sourced from the Cyber Hymnal / NoteWorthy Composer, in its
// original two-part texture -- unaltered except for transposition into each of
// the 12 keys:
//   - MIDI channel 0 (right hand): the hymn's melody line, exactly as written.
//   - MIDI channel 1 (left hand): the hymn's own accompaniment line, exactly as
//     written -- not simplified into block triads the way the Power in the
//     Blood lesson's left hand was, so some chords in this arrangement are
//     dominant 7th and fully-diminished 7th chords rather than plain triads
//     (see the Dominant 7th and Diminished 7th Chord lessons).
